<p><strong>Name:</strong> Dr. Roy G. Caroll</p>
<p><strong>Security Clearance:</strong> Level-2</p>
<p><strong>Occupation:</strong> General researcher.</p>
<p><strong>History:</strong> Dr. Caroll was recruited to the Foundation at 23 years of age. During this time, Caroll was still in university studying theoretical physics and zoology. Caroll then completed his degree while in Foundation employment with the assistance of research specialists.</p>
<p>Dr. Caroll has been in Foundation employment for five years and is now age 28.</p>
<p><strong>Additional Information:</strong> Dr. Caroll is currently undergoing investigation for possible anomalous abilities. The ability in question is the ability to attract and/or manifest organisms of the <em>Coccinellidae</em> family (ladybugs) at will.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Researcher Note:</strong> I'm telling you, they just like me. Just because I always happen to have a stray ladybug on my shoulder, even while inside, doesn't mean I'm anomalous. Or, at least, I don't think so. But, hey, that would be pretty cool, right?</p>
<p>- Dr. Caroll</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-1" style="display:none">
<div style="text-align: center;"><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-3527">SCP-3527</a> - Incompetent Rap-Loving Bodysnatchers</strong><br />
<strong>Object Class:</strong> Euclid<br />
<strong>Posted:</strong> <span class="odate time_1522367255 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Mar 2018 23:47</span><br />
<strong>Rating:</strong> +43<br />
<em>I'm sorry to break it to you, but you are not Tupac.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<blockquote>
<p>This was my first skip, and it was also a coldpost. On top of that, it was somehow successful. I thought of it when something like this ran through my mind: &quot;Aliens are cool. Why haven't we been taken over yet? They've gotta exist&#8230; What if it's because they're incompetent?&quot; I was also listening to the Kendrick Lamar song showcased in the skip at the time of writing, and that's where &quot;rap-loving&quot; came from.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-3826">SCP-3826</a> - The Definition of Technophobia</strong><br />
<strong>Object Class:</strong> Euclid<br />
<strong>Posted:</strong> <span class="odate time_1523818048 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Apr 2018 18:47</span><br />
<strong>Rating:</strong> +30<br />
<em>They're building a portal&#8230; I tried to ask where it was going&#8230; &quot;the present.&quot;</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<blockquote>
<p>Roughly my fourth skip concept. I had thought of it because I wanted to write something about an arising conflict between the Church of the Broken God and the Sarkic Cults. Plus, Alaska. Who doesn't like Alaska? I mean, they don't have many ladybirds, but&#8230; you know. Alaska.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-3641">SCP-3641</a> - Remember <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Apollo-99</span> Nased</strong><br />
<strong>Object Class:</strong> Euclid<br />
<strong>Posted:</strong> <span class="odate time_1523994950 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">17 Apr 2018 19:55</span><br />
<strong>Rating:</strong> +30<br />
<em>He lied to me.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<blockquote>
<p>This is my first space-based skip, and I was (and still am) really confident in the idea. It originally went through two renditions before the final one was posted onto the main site. It was inspired by the Solway Spaceman, and was encouraged by the 2001 film &quot;A Space Oddysey.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-3534">SCP-3534</a> - Doomsyesterday</strong><br />
<strong>Object Class:</strong> Keter<br />
<strong>Posted:</strong> <span class="odate time_1526674921 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 May 2018 20:22</span><br />
<strong>Rating:</strong> +75<br />
<em>&quot;Your music fucking sucks,&quot; he said.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<blockquote>
<p>This is my entry for the Doomsday Contest as part of Team Mikasa consisting of <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stormbreath" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3075960); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3075960&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1604893088" alt="stormbreath" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3075960)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stormbreath" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3075960); return false;">stormbreath</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1956625&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1604893088" alt="DrChandra" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1956625)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;">DrChandra</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stallmantic" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3472766); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3472766&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1604893088" alt="Stallmantic" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3472766)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stallmantic" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3472766); return false;">Stallmantic</a></span> and I. It's based in the War on All Fronts canon and explains the origins of the Crocosquid alongside its true Fifthist nature.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-3830">SCP-3830</a> - Sleeping With The Fishes</strong><br />
<strong>Object Class:</strong> Safe<br />
<strong>Posted:</strong> <span class="odate time_1527207589 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">25 May 2018 00:19</span><br />
<strong>Rating:</strong> +30<br />
<em>Get put to sleep <strong>by</strong> the fishes.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<blockquote>
<p>My first Safe-class article. I wanted to write an article about fish food for some reason, and then <span class="error-inline"><em>Dr_Aers</em> does not match any existing user name</span> dropped me with the dreaming concept and I altered it to be a betta fish doll. Then the rest kind of wrote itself.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-1131-j">SCP-1131-J</a> - <em>It works guys! Trust me!</em></strong><br />
<strong>Object Class:</strong> Thaumiel<br />
<strong>Posted:</strong> <span class="odate time_1528004712 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 Jun 2018 05:45</span><br />
<strong>Rating:</strong> +122<br />
<em><strong>SCP-055:</strong> Well shit.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<blockquote>
<p>I always wanted to make an article about tinfoil hats. Truthfully, it started out as a -EX, but I just found it way too funny to make it serious 100% of the time. It's also my first ever attempted joke article.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-3851">SCP-3851</a> - You May Not Be Able To Drown Your Demons, But The Demons Can Drown Your Screams</strong><sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-921928-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-921928-1')">1</a></sup><br />
<strong>Object Class:</strong> Safe<br />
<strong>Posted:</strong> <span class="odate time_1528771266 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Jun 2018 02:41</span><br />
<strong>Rating:</strong> +46<br />
<em>We are running out of food, heat, and, ironically, water.</em></p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-921928-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-921928-1')">1</a>. This title is purely based off of the title for the SCP found right above it in the Series IV list.</div>
</div>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<blockquote>
<p>This is the second to an upcoming series that I plan on making quite creepy. Big thanks to my friend Kyle for helping me with the concept! The prologue to this SCP is <a href="/every-last-drop">Every Last Drop</a> and probably won't make sense unless you read that.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-4315">SCP-4315</a> - S.C.P. Lovecraft</strong><br />
<strong>Object Class:</strong> Keter<br />
<strong>Posted:</strong> <span class="odate time_1541440772 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">05 Nov 2018 17:59</span><br />
<strong>Rating:</strong> +70<br />
<em>GRINDINGGRINDINGGRINDINGGRINDINGLIKEABABYCRYING</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<blockquote>
<p>My first Series V article and quite a pleasure to make with Gears. I personally really like how this turned out and it's my longest skip to date. I always wanted to write about history, and the 4k Contest finally allowed me to get the creative juices flowing.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-4655">SCP-4655</a> - Comfort Comes In Many Different Forms</strong><br />
<strong>Object Class:</strong> Safe<br />
<strong>Posted:</strong> <span class="odate time_1550710351 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 Feb 2019 00:52</span><br />
<strong>Rating:</strong> +45<br />
<em>We'll both miss her. Together.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<blockquote>
<p>My second Series V article which was written for creepy vibes. I had this idea in my head for a while now and finally decided to type it out and I'm pretty satisfied with the final product. It's my first time trying to focus on scaring the audience, so I hope it managed to deliver.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-4598">SCP-4598</a> - The Spiral Gestalt</strong><br />
<strong>Object Class:</strong> Euclid<br />
<strong>Posted:</strong> <span class="odate time_1552560564 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">14 Mar 2019 10:49</span><br />
<strong>Rating:</strong> +51<br />
<em>Er, stupid fucking mosquito.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<blockquote>
<p>I created this article not long after reading another JamCon entry. Sometimes, we just look too deep into song lyrics, and this is what happens when Dr. Hammond himself falls into the spiral gestalt because of some song.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/scp-4810">SCP-4810</a> - Hunt Stupid Game, Win Stupid Prizes</strong><br />
<strong>Object Class:</strong> Keter<br />
<strong>Posted:</strong> <span class="odate time_1558734396 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 May 2019 21:46</span><br />
<strong>Rating:</strong> +35<br />
<em>We didn't kill her. We just made her scared.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<blockquote>
<p>Another contest entry co-authored by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/gabriel-jade" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(414239); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=414239&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1604893088" alt="Gabriel Jade" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=414239)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/gabriel-jade" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(414239); return false;">Gabriel Jade</a></span>. I had a lot of fun in this contest and I managed to learn a hell of a lot about writing, both independently and cooperatively, by working with the members of Team Inkblots. I really enjoyed writing this one alongside Jade and the concept that we managed to come up with tied in nicely with my want to create an article involving something creepy and crawly.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-2" style="display:none">
<div style="text-align: center;"><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/every-last-drop">Every Last Drop</a></strong><br />
<strong>Posted:</strong> <span class="odate time_1528602674 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Jun 2018 03:51</span><br />
<strong>Rating:</strong> +35<br />
<em>I suppose it all started with one drop&#8230;</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<hr />
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="/the-light-will-attract-the-darkest-of-creatures">The Light Will Attract the Darkest of Creatures</a></strong><br />
<strong>Posted:</strong> <span class="odate time_1538441809 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Oct 2018 00:56</span><br />
<strong>Rating:</strong> +5<br />
<em>&#8230;it was the mysterious figure which stood before him, chowing down on the gory remains of Trey's puppy.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div></div>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-3" style="display:none">
<p>No, I'm not Arabic. I just like the aesthetic of Arabic words, both in English and in Arabic.</p>
<p>Hello! I'm <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drcaroll" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3828846); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3828846&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1604893088" alt="DrCaroll" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3828846)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drcaroll" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3828846); return false;">DrCaroll</a></span> and, while I have only been a member of this wiki for less than a month (at the time of writing this page), I've been involved in the SCP community for about three and a half years now. Unlike the majority of people, I wasn't actually pulled in by SCP:CB; I didn't even know what that was three and a half years ago.</p>
<p>I gained knowledge of this wonderful community through a roleplay server on Garry's Mod. Originally, I was just a D-Class, and so I had thought it was some sort of prison roleplay server. I still enjoyed it nonetheless.</p>
<p>After that, I noticed there were monstrosities that I was taken to see. I had no idea what they were, and so I asked out-of-character. They, of course, replied with &quot;it's an SCP,&quot; and I googled this wiki. Through the wiki, I gained knowledge of SCP:CB. Gotta be honest, though: not really a fan.</p>
<p>I just continued to roleplay on Garry's Mod until I officially decided to join the wiki and contribute myself. I absolutely love this community, and I am always willing to help anyone with anything they might need help with.</p>
<p>Don't be afraid to DM me if you have any inquiries! I'm also Junior Staff on Forum Crit, so DM me if you have a draft that you would like reviewed.</p>
</div>
</div>
